    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In fact, this is not strictly related to in-place ops, since\n\n```\ndf.loc[0, 'oth'] = df.loc[0, 'oth'] + 1\n```\n\nresults in the same behaviour. I bet it has to do instead with the fact that `df.loc[0, 'oth']` returns a `Series` (of 1 element) rather than a number (as `df.loc[0, ('oth', '')]`), and this is incoherent for instance with `df.loc[:,'oth']` and `df['oth']`, which both return a `Series` (not a `DataFrame`): that is they return the same as `df.loc[:, ('oth', '')]`.\n\nRetitling accordingly.\n"
